The following graph causes a problem with tail label placement:

```
node a {
	layering.layerConstraint: FIRST
	portConstraints: FIXED_SIDE
	
	port in { ^port.side: WEST }
}

node b {
	layering.layerConstraint: LAST
	portConstraints: FIXED_SIDE
	
	port out { ^port.side: EAST }
}

edge b.out -> a.in {
	label "A tail label with a bit of text" {
		edgeLabels.placement: TAIL
	}
}
```

Instead of a properly placed tail label, we get this:

![Screenshot 2019-08-08 at 11 08 04](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/7465584/62690344-d59fd700-b9cc-11e9-9126-cdbdf74db6f9.png)

Several problems here:

* The label has not had enough horizontal space reserved for it.
* The label's y coordinate is wrong.
* In fact, subsequent layout invocations cause the label to move rightwards and downwards, so the label's position is not even stable.

